1
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:18,280
Slow down, slow down.

2
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,519
Miss Nana, drink it while it's hot.

3
00:01:20,879 --> 00:01:21,640
He made it, didn't he?

4
00:01:22,159 --> 00:01:22,680
I don't have an appetite.

5
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:23,840
I made it.

6
00:01:24,159 --> 00:01:25,680
I used our most famous tea here,

7
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:26,599
the Himalayan sacred tea,

8
00:01:26,599 --> 00:01:27,359
to brew this milk tea.

9
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:28,680
Paired with these snacks,

10
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:29,239
it's so delicious.

11
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:30,280
Let me tell you,

12
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:31,359
you're really lucky.

13
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:32,319
The weather's been great these days.

14
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:34,200
Soon you'll be able to see Namjagbarwa Peak.

15
00:01:34,799 --> 00:01:35,599
Who's calling me?

16
00:01:37,159 --> 00:01:38,000
Hello, Bro Haozi.

17
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:39,519
I'm busy here. If it's important, make it quick.

18
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:40,159
Qian Qian,

19
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,519
I really still need a guest commentator.

20
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,680
Can you talk to Miss Nana again for me?

21
00:01:45,959 --> 00:01:47,319
You think she'll listen to me?

22
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:48,280
Right?

23
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:49,959
Don't even mention it.

24
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,000
She's acting like a diva.

25
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,239
The fee's too small for her.

26
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:53,920
Just shut up.

27
00:01:54,159 --> 00:01:54,599
Hanging up.

28
00:01:56,239 --> 00:01:57,560
That guy's not too bright.

29
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:58,799
I've got things to do, I'm off.

30
00:01:59,280 --> 00:01:59,719
Wait a moment.

31
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:03,200
That chef of yours,

32
00:02:03,599 --> 00:02:04,400
Jimei,

33
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,840
will he be there during the livestream?

34
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:07,879
Of course.

35
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:09,719
He's our head chef here.

36
00:02:10,159 --> 00:02:12,199
I'm telling you, his food is amazing.

37
00:02:15,159 --> 00:02:15,599
I'll take it.

38
00:02:17,199 --> 00:02:17,719
Really?

39
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,159
I'll call Bro Haozi right now.

40
00:02:21,159 --> 00:02:22,360
Thank you, Nana.

41
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,319
You, you, you have to come!

42
00:02:45,759 --> 00:02:46,240
Bro Jimei.

43
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,319
You're back just in time.

44
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:50,400
Try my saffron golden soup.

45
00:02:52,479 --> 00:02:52,960
How is it?

46
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:59,039
Like summer snowmelt running down my throat.

47
00:02:59,039 --> 00:02:59,960
Speak plainly, would you?

48
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,960
It tastes like medicine. Not good.

49
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:07,199
Today's gastrodia

50
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:10,520
has the numbness but no soul.

51
00:03:12,159 --> 00:03:13,080
The gastrodia back then

52
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,840
had this earthy, raw scent.

53
00:03:15,759 --> 00:03:18,639
One bite and you'd taste the forest.

54
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:23,240
That feeling is gone for good.

55
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:27,039
Well, it's not entirely gone.

56
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,680
The other day, Medo and I were up the back hill.

57
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,919
We saw gastrodia growing under a tree, really...

58
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,319
Getting carried away again, aren't you?

59
00:03:33,639 --> 00:03:35,400
That's a nationally protected plant.

60
00:03:35,639 --> 00:03:36,639
Dig it up and you'll go to jail.

61
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:37,319
Didn't you know?

62
00:03:37,719 --> 00:03:39,039
I know, I know.

63
00:03:43,639 --> 00:03:44,240
Forget it then.

64
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:00,919
Who is it?

65
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:10,680
Who's there?

66
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:11,759
It's me.

67
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,879
Just come on in.

68
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,439
What do you want?

69
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:27,839
I came to bring you this.

70
00:04:30,439 --> 00:04:31,199
What's that smell?

71
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,639
Just take it back.

72
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,560
It's an old remedy from my mother.

73
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,519
Works wonders for bruises.

74
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,600
I have a spray.

75
00:04:37,199 --> 00:04:38,360
Sprays only treat the skin.

76
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:39,279
Not the muscles and bones.

77
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,040
Here.

78
00:04:42,319 --> 00:04:43,480
See? That hurts, doesn't it?

79
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,439
And you said you didn't need it.

80
00:04:45,839 --> 00:04:46,279
No, wait.

81
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,000
This is the foot I hurt.

82
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,519
Let me help you over there.

83
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:53,600
It's awkward here. Come on.

84
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,079
Easy, easy.

85
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,160
This medicine needs to be applied hot.

86
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,120
You're holding back.

87
00:05:16,439 --> 00:05:16,879
Let me.

88
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:37,879
Did I press too hard?

89
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,519
It's fine.

90
00:05:53,879 --> 00:05:55,519
You... if it hurts, just yell out.

91
00:06:21,839 --> 00:06:23,199
Hang in there, almost done.

92
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,040
Get some good rest.

93
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,240
You'll be up and about tomorrow.

94
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,399
Okay.

95
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:54,800
I'll come back tomorrow to apply it again.

96
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:58,920
Oh, right.

97
00:06:59,639 --> 00:07:01,079
About Bro Jimei's soup,

98
00:07:01,079 --> 00:07:02,800
the flavor's always a bit off.

99
00:07:03,279 --> 00:07:04,639
If we don't use gastrodia,

100
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:06,040
is there any other way?

101
00:07:09,319 --> 00:07:10,279
There's a red mushroom

102
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:12,399
whose mycelium often grows with gastrodia.

103
00:07:12,439 --> 00:07:13,680
The taste is about 70-80% similar.

104
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,519
If you pair it with the soil beside the mushroom

105
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:17,720
and slow-roast it...

106
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,079
You're saying as long as the soil's right

107
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,000
and the mushroom's right,

108
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,439
we can fool the taste buds?

109
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,000
Alright.

110
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:27,879
You get some good rest then.

111
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:28,759
I'll be heading off.

112
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:47,920
Thank you.

113
00:07:48,959 --> 00:07:49,519
I'm leaving.

114
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:33,159
Get a good sleep here.

115
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:45,120
The gastrodia back then had this earthy, raw scent.

116
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:47,600
One bite and you'd taste the forest.

117
00:08:48,559 --> 00:08:49,559
That feeling...

118
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,080
is gone for good.

119
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:20,120
Medo.

120
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Your leg hasn't even healed yet.

121
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,080
Why are you out here?

122
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,600
I've been looking everywhere for you.

123
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,919
Don't worry, I'm fine.

124
00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:27,879
By the way,

125
00:09:28,279 --> 00:09:29,519
What did you need me for?

126
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,600
I've got great news for you.

127
00:09:31,879 --> 00:09:33,720
The district reviewed our proposal,

128
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,759
and they said if

129
00:09:35,879 --> 00:09:37,320
the wild plant conservation site is confirmed,

130
00:09:37,559 --> 00:09:39,879
they'll allocate support funds to our village.

131
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,759
Really?

132
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,519
That's wonderful!

133
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:45,000
I'm doing a drone patrol right now.

134
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:45,919
Here, take a look.

135
00:09:50,159 --> 00:09:50,960
Right here.

136
00:09:57,679 --> 00:09:59,039
Wait, why is there a hole here?

137
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:00,919
Did wild boars dig it up?

138
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,799
These are marks from a shovel.

139
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:08,360
Wild boars don't use shovels.
